host_about:
Not a real estate professional. Please be direct on your doubts and questions. Thank you!

35+yo engineer. Brazilian born, living in Canada for over 5 years. Currently (2018, 2nd semester) in Rio.

Passionate about travelling, have been to:
    (1) Americas - Argentina, Uruguay, Paraguay, Brazil, Peru, Venezuela, Mexico, Cuba, Puerto Rico, USA and Canada;
    (2) Africa & Middle East - South Africa, Swaziland, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Zambia, Egypt, Israel, Jordan and Turkey;
    (3) Asia - India, China (incl. Hong Kong), Japan and Thailand;
    (4) Europe - Portugal, Spain, France, Italy, Austria, Germany and Netherlands.

I am early retired microchip engineer who moved to Paradise (it is how I call Hawaii). I love this place and want to share my love with other people. 
House is very secluded in a jungles in Fern Forest on a Volcano slope just 8 miles away from Volcano national park.
Unlike other B&B owners I am suggesting per your choice VIP-tours, renting a house/room (Bed and Breakfast), renting cars, fishing, hunting, whale watching, etc. in one bundle.
 Basic price for each bedroom is $89-99/night (two people). You can rent one or up to four bedrooms or entire house.
Extra guests/children can sleep on couches for basic price $20/night/guest.
If you rent two bedrooms (or just one, but without other guests), you actually have in your possession entire floor. If it is one bedroom (Master Suite), usually it is first floor with gigantic hall and porch with Jacuzzi. If it is two bedrooms - usually it is second floor with living.
Shared areas are kitchen, dining room, big covered porch with grill, office on a second floor that you have to share with other guests (if they are here) and owners who live on premises.
If you are renting room/rooms for 7 days or more - you are eligible for 10% discount;
If you are renting entire house (4 bedrooms) - you are eligible for another 10% discount;
If you are renting for a month or more - you are eligible for another 10% discount.
Sure, if you choose a bundle, you save your $$, time and nervous. For more information, please, see (Website hidden by Airbnb) and (Website hidden by Airbnb) 
There is a German Shepherd dog on premises.
Bed and Breakfast becoming more and more popular in America due to more comfort, privacy for less cost.

Choosing us you get following advantages:
1. We are local, so, you saving at least $150-250 for airfare ticket of your guide from another place;
2. We are local, so, we can show you hidden "pearls" that other guides even didn't hear about;
3. We are flexible - we can build your tours  according to your taste, mood, budget;
4. We can meet you at airport and bring back for a small charge;
5. If you have big group for special event, etc., we can place up to 16 people;
6. We are placed next to Volcano National Park in very quite secluded jungles (between Hilo and Kona), so, you can relax from noise and vanity of crowds and save time/money in your trips and have a good sleep during cool evening/nights in mountains without insects and noise.
